|CKBCook Ash: Waste Not, Warn Nobody|000

Syntax: cookash <grey|red|blue|mixed>
Alias:  ccook

At Rank 2 and Volatility 1, use an acid flask made with 'brewacid' and empty
all relevant ash from a carried corpse burner into it. A single-colour batch
needs at least 10 matching ash. Mixed needs at least 10 of every colour and
empties all three stores.

  Grey   - Alchemy 25; accuracy and defensive footwork
  Red    - Alchemy 75; direct combat damage
  Blue   - Alchemy 75; accuracy and one extra swing
  Mixed  - Alchemy 150; a smaller blend of red and blue benefits

Aim for 100 ash when you want a proper batch. Feeding it more still stretches
the rush, but the difference soon becomes difficult to notice. The resulting
owner-bound vial goes flat after two hours. Quaffing starts a Cookash Rush
shown in 'buffs'; only one rush can be active. Throwing the cooked vial keeps
its elemental surprise and always splashes the Charlatan too. This is called
quality control. The cloak needs only a few seconds before it can cook another,
provided you have another acid flask and enough ash.
